        "text": "; see especially vers. 41-44 and Leviticus 20:25; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 14:3-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Peter's astonishment must, therefore, have been exceeding great at the command to slay and eat. And so his answer in ver. 14 shows. And yet our Lord had taught him the same truth (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 15:10-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or still more distinctly ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 8:14-23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Acts 10:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
